parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak from Top of Fuel Tank
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak from the top of the fuel tank can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the top of the fuel tank

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Hesitation and Stalling after Refueling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine hesitation and stalling after refueling can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving in heavy traffic.
A defective liquid/vapor separator valve can cause engine hesitation and stalling, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents.
Corrosion-related fuel pump failure can cause engine stalling, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to safety risks, inconvenience, and potential accidents.
The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the actual fuel level, leading to potential safety risks, such as running out of fuel on the road.
The failure of the ECM can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to safety risks, such as loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to shut off suddenly, leading to safety risks, such as accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle shuts off when touching the key in the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the composite piston caliper can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a loss of braking power, increased stopping distance, and potentially, accidents.
symptoms: smoke pouring out of the wheel wells

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incorrect tolerance of brake pads can cause the caliper to not retract properly, leading to overheating, brake failure, and potentially, accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wedge against the rotor-disc

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust and corrosion in the rear brakes can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, increased stopping distance, and potentially, accidents.
